From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 11:16:56 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] configs: iot2050: Add SPL FDT padding

The K3 SPL performs reserved-memory fixups on the control DTB before
Driver Model scans it. Those fixups may add or replace reserved-memory
nodes and therefore need writable space beyond the packed DTB.

Configure 8192 bytes of DTC padding for IOT2050 so the SPL control DTB
keeps writable space for reserved-memory fixups after fdtgrep
processing.

Signed-off-by: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
---
 configs/iot2050_defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/configs/iot2050_defconfig b/configs/iot2050_defconfig
index ee0939c09864..02ef5e5e8b77 100644
--- a/configs/iot2050_defconfig
+++ b/configs/iot2050_defconfig
@@ -3,6 +3,7 @@ CONFIG_SKIP_LOWLEVEL_INIT=y
 CONFIG_ARCH_K3=y
 # CONFIG_TI_SECURE_DEVICE is not set
 CONFIG_SYS_MALLOC_F_LEN=0x8000
+CONFIG_SYS_DTC_PAD_BYTES=8192
 CONFIG_SPL_GPIO=y
 CONFIG_SPL_LIBCOMMON_SUPPORT=y
 CONFIG_SOC_K3_AM654=y
